\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Pointers to Structures\
\
\pard\pardeftab720

\b0\fs28 \cf0 Like any other type, structures can be pointed by its own type of pointers.\
\

\b Arrow Pperator (->)
\b0 \
\

\f1\fs24 This is a dereference operator that is used exclusively with pointers to objects with members. This operator serves to access a member of an object to which we have a reference.\
\

\f0\b\fs32 Example:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720

\f2\b0\fs28 \cf2 pmovie->title 
\f5\b \cf0 ==
\f2\b0 \cf2  (*pmovie).title\
\
\pard\pardeftab720

